reviews.review:
At the beginning of this game there was hope. It WAS a nice game. Later on they published some updates that actually ruined it for me. They make it easier for the killer and the survivors and take away all the difficult parts.  Why should you cook food if you can order food huh? Well.. I'm lazy, but not that lazy. 

Some things that ruined it for me in the recently updates:
- The new user interface makes it easier to bind a survivor character to a player name. Why should you do that? If you need to survive then you also have almost no tools. Otherwise you cant say that you need to survive;
- The challenging part to know how many times someone got on the hook is gone;
- If you are for the second time on the hook then you have to just press space and hit the white bar instead of spamming space;
- There are no immediate consequences if missing a white bar on the second hook.

Overall I think that they almost got rid of the most challenging parts of the game. If feels like I need to survive while carying a bag with all the stuff I need to survive.
